<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900926-0050</DOCNO><DOCID>900926-0050.</DOCID><HL>   Treasury Plans Offer   Of Short-Term Bills   To Raise $1.45 Billion</HL><DATE>09/26/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C17</SO><IN>CDS, INTEREST RATES, COMMERCIAL PAPER (FIN)BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)</IN><GV>TREASURY DEPARTMENT (TRE)</GV><LP>   WASHINGTON -- The Treasury plans to raise $1.45 billion innew cash with the sale Monday of about $18.4 billion inshort-term bills to redeem $16.96 billion in maturing bills.   However, the Treasury will postpone the auction unless ithas assurances that the debt ceiling will be raised.</LP><TEXT>   The offering will be divided evenly between 13-week and26-week bills maturing on Jan. 3, 1991, and April 4, 1991,respectively. The bills will be available in minimumdenominations of $10,000.   Tenders must be received by 1 p.m. EDT Monday at theTreasury or at Federal Reserve banks or branches.</TEXT></DOC>